# HERMES Frontend Environment Variables for GitHub Pages Deployment
# These should be set as repository secrets in GitHub Actions
# Go to: Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions

# Backend connection (required for full functionality)
VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://your-hermes-app.onrender.com
VITE_BACKEND_WS_URL=wss://your-hermes-app.onrender.com

# Deployment environment  
VITE_ENVIRONMENT=production

# Additional configuration (optional)
# VITE_ANALYTICS_URL=https://your-analytics-service.com
# VITE_SUPPORT_EMAIL=support@your-law-firm.com

# Instructions:
# 1. Deploy your backend using the "Deploy to Render" button in README.md
# 2. Copy your backend URL from the deployment
# 3. Add these as GitHub repository secrets (without the # and VITE_ prefix)
# 4. Push any change to trigger a new GitHub Pages build
# 5. Your demo will now connect to your backend for full voice functionality